  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through various methods, including:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing know-your-customer (KYC) regulations\n- Establishing mandatory reporting thresholds\n\n2. Law Enforcement Investigations\n- Specialized financial crime units\n- Forensic accounting techniques\n- International cooperation between agencies\n\n3. Regulatory Frameworks\n- Bank secrecy act compliance\n- International standards like FATF recommendations\n- Strict penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Advanced Technology\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Data analytics to detect patterns\n- Machine learning algorithms\n\n5. Criminal Prosecutions\n- Asset seizure\n- Substantial financial penalties\n- Potential imprisonment\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute complex money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and technological strategies.",
